<head>



<title>DIRECTION-TO-ALIGN-WITH-OTHERS-D</title>

</head>



<body>



<div id="bodyContent">

	

	<h3><i>I schedule the

	<a title="DIRECTION-TO-ALIGN-WITH-OTHERS" href="DIRECTION-TO-ALIGN-WITH-OTHERS.html">

	DIRECTION-TO-ALIGN-WITH-OTHERS</a> micro-behaviour to happen after the

	<a title="DIRECTION-TO-AVOID-OTHERS" href="DIRECTION-TO-AVOID-OTHERS.html">

	DIRECTION-TO-AVOID-OTHERS</a> micro-behaviour.</i> </h3>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin micro-behaviour</font>
	<p><b>DIRECTION-TO-ALIGN-WITH-OTHERS-DELAYED </b></p>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin NetLogo code:</font>
	<pre>do-after .001
   [add-behaviour <a title="DIRECTION-TO-ALIGN-WITH-OTHERS" href="DIRECTION-TO-ALIGN-WITH-OTHERS.html">DIRECTION-TO-ALIGN-WITH-OTHERS</a>]
</pre>

	<font size="2" color="gray">End NetLogo code</font>
	<h2><span class="mw-headline">Variants </span></h2>

	<p>You can delay by any amount of time. Here we delay by .001 time units.

	</p>

	<h2><span class="mw-headline">Related Micro-behaviours </span></h2>

	<p>

	<a title="DIRECTION-TO-ALIGN-WITH-OTHERS" href="DIRECTION-TO-ALIGN-WITH-OTHERS.html">

	DIRECTION-TO-ALIGN-WITH-OTHERS</a> does the real work. </p>

	<h2><span class="mw-headline">How this works </span></h2>

	<p>It schedules

	<a title="DIRECTION-TO-ALIGN-WITH-OTHERS" href="DIRECTION-TO-ALIGN-WITH-OTHERS.html">

	DIRECTION-TO-ALIGN-WITH-OTHERS</a> to start .001 time units from now. When 

	it runs it then schedules itself for the next <i>delta-t</i>. The purpose of 

	this is to be sure that

	<a title="DIRECTION-TO-AVOID-OTHERS" href="DIRECTION-TO-AVOID-OTHERS.html">

	DIRECTION-TO-AVOID-OTHERS</a> runs first. </p>

	<h2><span class="mw-headline">History </span></h2>

	<p>This was implemented by Ken Kahn. </div>



